              <p class="card-text">Comprehensive estate planning including tax optimization, trust structures, and strategies to minimize inheritance tax for your beneficiaries.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4 col-12 mb-4">
          <div class="card h-100">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h5 class="card-title">Will Updates & Reviews</h5>
              <p class="card-text">Regular review and updating of your Spanish will to reflect changes in circumstances, law, or family situations.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container px-4 py-5">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12">
          <h2 class="pb-4 m-3 text-center">Understanding Spanish Succession Law</h2>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6 col-12">
          <h4>Forced Heirship Rules</h4>
          <p>Spanish law includes forced heirship provisions that reserve a portion of your estate for certain family members. We help you understand these rules and plan accordingly to protect your spouse and chosen beneficiaries.</p>
          
          <h4>Legitimate Portion</h4>
          <p>Two-thirds of your Spanish estate must go to your children or descendants under Spanish law. We advise on strategies to maximize the portion available to your spouse or other beneficiaries.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6 col-12">
          <h4>Spousal Protection</h4>
          <p>Spanish succession law can leave surviving spouses with less inheritance than expected. We provide strategies to ensure your spouse is adequately protected within Spanish legal requirements.</p>
          
          <h4>International Coordination</h4>
          <p>We ensure your Spanish will coordinates properly with your UK will and other international assets to create a comprehensive estate plan that works across jurisdictions.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-light">
    <div class="container px-4 py-5">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12">
          <h2 class="pb-4 m-3 text-center">The Spanish Will Process</h2>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6 col-12">
          <h4>1. Initial Consultation</h4>
          <p>We discuss your assets, family situation, and wishes to understand your estate planning needs and objectives.</p>
          
          <h4>2. Legal Analysis</h4>
          <p>Comprehensive analysis of Spanish succession law implications for your specific situation and coordination with existing UK wills.</p>
          
          <h4>3. Will Drafting</h4>
          <p>Expert drafting of your Spanish will to comply with Spanish law while maximizing protection for your chosen beneficiaries.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6 col-12">
          <h4>4. Notary Execution</h4>
          <p>Arrangement and attendance at Spanish notary for proper execution and witnessing of your Spanish will.</p>
          
          <h4>5. Registration</h4>
          <p>Registration of your will with the Spanish Central Will Registry to ensure it can be easily located when needed.</p>
          
          <h4>6. Ongoing Support</h4>
          <p>Regular reviews and updates to ensure your will remains current and effective as circumstances change.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

